itBranch\":\"alisha/e2e-triage\",\"slug\":\"pure-napping-orbit\",\"type\":\"user\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":[{\"tool_use_id\":\"toolu_01BtgxmBcLCke1MFkkXMQH6T\",\"type\":\"tool_result\",\"content\":\"The file /Users/alisha/Projects/devenv/cli/.claude/skills/e2e-triage/README.md has been updated successfully.\"}]},\"uuid\":\"2f895f54-e1c9-4dae-85ae-0d37ee926587\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-06T22:46:56.588Z\",\"toolUseResult\":{\"filePath\":\"/Users/alisha/Projects/devenv/cli/.claude/skills/e2e-triage/README.md\",\"oldString\":\"## Key Files\",\"newString\":\"## Related Skills\\n\\n- `/debug-e2e` — Standalone artifact analysis for diagnosing a specific failure. Use when you already have artifacts and want to understand *what went wrong* without re-running or classifying.\\n- `/e2e-triage` uses debug-e2e's workflow internally for its analysis step, then adds classification (flaky vs real-bug) and automated action (fixes/PRs/issues).\\n\\n## Key Files\",\"originalFile\":\"# E2E Triage Skill\\n\\nTriage E2E test failures by re-running tests, classifying failures as flaky vs real-bug, and taking appropriate action (fixes in local mode, PRs/issues in CI mode).\\n\\n## Two Modes\\n\\n| Mode | Trigger | Action on flaky | Action on real-bug |\\n|------|---------|----------------|--------------------|\\n| **Local** | User invokes `/e2e-triage` | Presents findings, applies fixes in working tree | Presents root cause analysis, applies fix if approved |\\n| **CI** | `WORKFLOW_RUN_ID` env var set (via `e2e-triage.yml`) | Creates batched PR | Creates or comments on GitHub issue |\\n\\n## Local Usage\\n\\n```\\n# Triage a specific test\\n/e2e-triage TestInteractiveMultiStep\\n\\n# Triage a specific test for one agent\\n/e2e-triage TestInteractiveMultiStep --agent claude-code\\n\\n# Triage multiple tests\\n/e2e-triage TestInteractiveMultiStep TestCheckpointRewind\\n\\n# Analyze existing artifacts (skip re-running)\\n/e2e-triage /path/to/artifact/dir\\n\\n# Download lastest CI run artifacts and triage\\n/e2e-triage get latest CI run\\n```\\n\\nThe skill will:\\n1. Run the test(s) up to 3 times (first run, re-run on failure, tiebreaker if split)\\n2. Analyze artifacts (`console.log`, `entire.log`, `git-log.txt`, checkpoint metadata)\\n3. Classify each failure and present findings\\n4. Ask before applying any fixes\\n\\n## CI Mode\\n\\nTriggered automatically by the `e2e-triage.yml` workflow. Downloads artifacts, re-runs failures via `e2e-isolated.yml`, then:\\n- **Flaky fixes** — batched into a single PR (`fix/e2e-flaky-<id>`)\\n- **Real bugs** — filed as GitHub issues (with dedup check)\\n- **Summary** — writes `triage-summary.json` for Slack notifications\\n\\n## Classification Logic\\n\\nRe-run results are the primary signal:\\n\\n| Pattern | Classification |\\n|---------|---------------|\\n| FAIL / PASS / PASS | Flaky |\\n| FAIL / PASS / FAIL | Flaky (non-deterministic) |\\n| FAIL / FAIL / PASS | Flaky (non-deterministic) |\\n| FAIL / FAIL / FAIL | Real-bug OR flaky (test-bug) — depends on root cause location |\\n\\n**Key distinction for consistent failures:** if the root cause is in `cmd/entire/cli/` (product code), it's a **real-bug**. If it's in `e2e/` (test infra), it's **flaky (test-bug)**.\\n\\n## Key Files\\n\\n- `SKILL.md` — Full skill definition with all steps, classification rules, and action templates\\n- `../../.github/workflows/e2e-triage.yml` — CI workflow that triggers CI mode\\n- `../../scripts/download-e2e-artifacts.sh` — Downloads artifacts from CI runs\\n\",\"structuredPatch\":[{\"oldStart\":54,\"oldLines\":6,\"newStart\":54,\"newLines\":11,\"lines\":[\" \",\" **Key distinction for consistent failures:** if the root cause is in `cmd/entire/cli/` (product code), it's a **real-bug**. If it's in `e2e/` (test infra), it's **flaky (test-bug)**.\",\" \",\"+## Related Skills\",\"+\",\"+- `/debug-e2e` — Standalone artifact analysis for diagnosing a specific failure. Use when you already have artifacts and want to understand *what went wrong* without re-running or classifying.\",\"+- `/e2e-triage` uses debug-e2e's workflow internally for its analysis step, then adds classification (flaky vs real-bug) and automated action (fixes/PRs/issues).\",\"+\",\" ## Key Files\",\" \",\" - `SKILL.md` — Full skill definition with all steps, classification rules, and action templates\"]}],\"userModified\":false,\"replaceAll\":false},\"sourceToolAssistantUUID\":\"03d06e77-ffdd-4f96-8399-c4fe0613a4c9\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"2f895f54-e1c9-4dae-85ae-0d37ee926587\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/alisha/Projects/devenv/cli\",\"sessionId\":\"95a06d90-7dbf-4a73-9806-8f32e8421f7b\",\"version\":\"2.1.70\",\"gitBranch\":\"alisha/e2e-triage\",\"slug\":\"pure-napping-orbit\",\"message\":{\"model\":\"claude-opus-4-6\",\"id\":\"msg_016JN1bgUi4oTiAA9xFFdGUA\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Let me verify the debug-e2e SKILL.md has the steps 2-5 we're referencing.\"}],\"stop_reason\":null,\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":1,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":2365,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":34777,\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0,\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":2365},\"output_tokens\":1,\"service_tier\":\"standard\",\"inference_geo\":\"not_available\"}},\"requestId\":\"req_011CYne4ZmsKZBaYA5k3GMVE\",\"type\":\"assistant\",\"uuid\":\"e8e2ec7e-05b6-4c5f-84be-c8ad9dfa85fe\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-06T22:46:59.520Z\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"e8e2ec7e-05b6-4c5f-84be-c8ad9dfa85fe\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/alisha/Projects/devenv/cli\",\"sessionId\":\"95a06d90-7dbf-4a73-9806-8f32e8421f7b\",\"version\":\"2.1.70\",\"gitBranch\":\"alisha/e2e-triage\",\"slug\":\"pure-napping-orbit\",\"message\":{\"model\":\"claude-opus-4-6\",\"id\":\"msg_016JN1bgUi4oTiAA9xFFdGUA\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"id\":\"toolu_01B4Be3pZ6CicN